Workday Names Robynne Sisco New CFO
The provider of human-resource and finance software has been posting losses in recent quarters as it invests in global expansion

 






By

Joshua Jamerson


Joshua Jamerson
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyJoshua Jamerson
@joshjame
joshua.jamerson@wsj.com




  April 12, 2016 9:34 a.m. ET





Cloud-based service provider Workday Inc. named Robynne Sisco as its chief financial officer, elevating a corporate finance and accounting veteran as the firm expands. Ms. Sisco will report to co-president Mark Peek, who had served concurrently as finance chief until Ms. Sisco’s appointment.  “Robynne has a clear understanding of the...
  


